uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.transition

Class TransitionKey<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.transition.TransitionKey<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - parameter type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AppUserKey, DynamicFormTransitionKey, LogFactory.EntryKey, PartTransitionKey, PersonalResponseKey, ResponseTransitionKey, TableTransitionKey, XMLKey

    public class TransitionKey<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    General purpose key class used to key transitions. Transitions can be keyed by any class and enums are often used for this. This class is useful where the set of transitions may come from multiple sources e.g. when sub-classes define additional transitions. TransitionKey objects are parameterised by a target type. Though this is usually the target type of the Transitions it can be any type that uniquely identifies the set of transitions.
